`$result` contains an _array_ of strings.

While `$result.split(&quot;:&quot;)` does apply splitting to the each element (courtesy of [*member enumeration*](https://stackoverflow.com/a/44620191/45375)), it simply _concatenates_ the resulting token arrays, returning a _single, flat_ array.

Therefore, applying indexing to that flat array - `[3,4,6]` - returns only 3 elements _in total_, across all elements, which is not your intent.

Instead, **you must iterate over the elements of `$result` and split and slice _each element_**:

```
$(
  foreach ($line in $result) {
    $line.Split(&#39;:&#39;)[3, 4, 6]
  }
) | Out-File -LiteralPath .\output.txt

