You can actually do this with [aggregation framework][1]. The operation you need to run consists of a pipeline on the `post` collection that does a [`$lookup`][2] to the `comments` collection and create an extra field that returns the count of the items in the array the [`$lookup`][2] pipeline step produces.

Consider running the following aggregate operation:

    def posts_with_comment_count():
        pipeline = [
            { &quot;$lookup&quot;: {
                &quot;from&quot;: &quot;comment&quot;,
                &quot;localField&quot;: &quot;_id&quot;,
                &quot;foreignField&quot;: &quot;post_id&quot;,
                &quot;as&quot;: &quot;comment_count&quot;
            } },
            { &quot;$addFields&quot;: {
                &quot;comment_count&quot;: { &quot;$size&quot;: &quot;$comment_count&quot; }
            } },
            { &quot;$sort&quot;: { &quot;_id&quot;: -1 } }
        ]
        posts = list(mongo.db.posts.aggregate(pipeline))

        return posts


  [1]: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/aggregation/
  [2]: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/lookup/

